import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='num_dependencies', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="source", y="num_dependencies", data=data, estimator=lambda x: len(x))
    chart.axhline(y=chart.get_yticks()[-1], color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max: {:.2f}'.format(data['num_dependencies'].max()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    target_freq = data['target'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=target_freq.index, y=target_freq.values, palette="Blues_d")
    plt.title('What is the most common target?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Target')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
